  "description": "The dish uses South Indian evening-tiffin logic: quick-cooking grains, legumes, and aromatic tempering for depth without richness. South Indian Sundal Salad Bowl brings a distinct structure, seasoning pattern, and grain-legume balance to the table.",
  "preparation": "",
  "cooking_steps": [
    "Heat oil in a soup pot over medium heat. Add onion, garlic, ginger, cumin, and pepper and cook 2 minutes until fragrant.",
    "Add the vegetable, pulse or grain accent, salt, and water. Bring to a boil, then reduce to low heat and simmer 18 minutes until the vegetables are fully tender.",
    "Blend lightly if the soup benefits from body, or leave chunky for a brothier finish.",
    "Adjust seasoning and serve hot as a complete light dinner."
  ],
